00:30:43.842 --> 00:30:46.970
CHIEF OH: You splashed alcohol on me
and acted like a drunkard.

534
00:30:47.053 --> 00:30:48.805
-That's all.
-Speak for yourself.

535
00:30:49.806 --> 00:30:51.099
(CHUCKLES)

536
00:30:53.977 --> 00:30:56.396
Sorry if I caused you any trouble.

537
00:30:59.190 --> 00:31:02.235
Geez, when did she record that?

538
00:31:02.318 --> 00:31:03.987
Seriously.

539
00:31:04.070 --> 00:31:06.948
CHIEF OH: You were so cute.
I couldn't help but record it.

540
00:31:07.699 --> 00:31:08.700
(SIGHS)

541
00:31:12.745 --> 00:31:15.582
I'll send you the cost
for Qingdao and the postnatal center.

542
00:31:15.665 --> 00:31:17.083
Send me your account number.

543
00:31:22.881 --> 00:31:25.383
What's she thinking?

544
00:31:26.092 --> 00:31:27.302
(MIRIM LAUGHS)

545
00:31:27.385 --> 00:31:28.386
Father.

546
00:31:28.469 --> 00:31:30.555
-Yura.
-(EXCITED CHATTER)

547
00:31:31.306 --> 00:31:32.932
MIRIM: I knew you were generous,

548
00:31:33.016 --> 00:31:36.102
but I didn't know you'd go this far.

549
00:31:36.185 --> 00:31:37.228
Yura.

550
00:31:37.312 --> 00:31:38.688
I'm not sure if I can take this.

551
00:31:38.771 --> 00:31:39.772
Take what?

552
00:31:39.856 --> 00:31:41.816
JIHOON: Don't act like you don't know.

553
00:31:41.900 --> 00:31:43.776
Chief Oh told us.

554
00:31:44.819 --> 00:31:45.820
Chief Oh?

555
00:31:45.904 --> 00:31:48.531
You told her if she's going to pay,
she better make it good.

556
00:31:48.615 --> 00:31:50.575
She just called and said she upgraded

557
00:31:50.658 --> 00:31:51.993
Dad's seat to first class.

558
00:31:52.869 --> 00:31:55.747
Thanks to you, I get to fly
to Qingdao on a bed.

559
00:31:55.830 --> 00:31:58.124
Suite room and a limo tour.

560
00:31:59.542 --> 00:32:01.753
I'm getting ahead. (LAUGHS)

561
00:32:01.836 --> 00:32:05.715
I'll be getting a whole body massage
in the postnatal center every day.

562
00:32:05.798 --> 00:32:08.176
From now on, my role model is you.

563
00:32:08.259 --> 00:32:09.928
Chief Oh sows,

564
00:32:10.011 --> 00:32:11.679
and you reap. (CLICKS TONGUE)

565
00:32:11.763 --> 00:32:14.057
(LAUGHS) Let's give it up for her.

566
00:32:14.140 --> 00:32:16.559
-(ALL CLAPPING)
-(YURA LAUGHING)

567
00:32:17.518 --> 00:32:18.519
MIRIM: Come on.

568
00:32:21.356 --> 00:32:22.899
JIHOON: She must be embarrassed.

569
00:32:22.982 --> 00:32:24.776
-She rushed in.
-I know.

570
00:32:24.859 --> 00:32:26.694
-Sit inside.
-Thanks.

571
00:32:29.113 --> 00:32:31.032
YURA: Oh, you don't have to.

572
00:32:31.115 --> 00:32:33.284
But since you don't feel comfortable,

573
00:32:33.368 --> 00:32:35.620
9,500,000 won.
I'm sending you my account number.

574
00:32:40.708 --> 00:32:43.378
What a lunatic.

575
00:32:46.255 --> 00:32:47.256
(SIGHS)

576
00:32:48.549 --> 00:32:50.468
YURA: I'll send it to you right away.

577
00:32:52.387 --> 00:32:54.430
I'll pay you 600,000 won on the first

578
00:32:54.514 --> 00:32:57.016
-of every month for 36 months.
-(LAUGHING)

579
00:32:58.017 --> 00:33:00.436
-She's funny.
-Dominic's tough.

580
00:33:00.520 --> 00:33:02.939
He has so many disguised identities.

581
00:33:03.022 --> 00:33:04.816
This prick... (SIGHS)

582
00:33:04.899 --> 00:33:07.276
He'll give us a pain in the neck
when he enters Korea.

583
00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:09.153
So we must get rid of him now.

584
00:33:09.237 --> 00:33:12.448
Some say he was in the MI6.

585
00:33:12.532 --> 00:33:14.534
Some say he was in Mossad.

586
00:33:16.035 --> 00:33:18.287
If Interpol suffered this much,

587
00:33:19.414 --> 00:33:21.290
are you sure we don't need backup?

588
00:33:22.667 --> 00:33:24.544
It's better for just us to move.

589
00:33:24.627 --> 00:33:27.005
Our goal is to dig into the group
through Dominic,

590
00:33:27.672 --> 00:33:29.048
but in the worst case scenario,

591
00:33:30.299 --> 00:33:31.592
we'd have to kill him.

592
00:33:32.719 --> 00:33:34.137
(IN ENGLISH) Okay.

593
00:33:45.898 --> 00:33:47.900
(STUDENTS CHATTERING)

594
00:33:47.984 --> 00:33:50.653
(IN KOREAN) Guys. Focus.

595
00:33:50.737 --> 00:33:52.321
You're finally performing tomorrow.

596
00:33:52.405 --> 00:33:53.531
Aren't you all nervous?

597
00:33:53.614 --> 00:33:55.950
-STUDENTS: Yes.
-Yes.

598
00:33:56.034 --> 00:33:58.119
When your parents come tomorrow,

599
00:33:58.202 --> 00:34:00.538
just show them what you worked on.

600
00:34:00.621 --> 00:34:01.622
Don't be nervous.

601
00:34:01.706 --> 00:34:03.416
STUDENTS: Okay.

602
00:34:03.499 --> 00:34:06.252
Don't pull Seoyeon's costume.

603
00:34:06.335 --> 00:34:10.298
-(SIGHS) He ripped it.
-My gosh.

604
00:34:10.381 --> 00:34:13.134
The performance is tomorrow.
Why would you rip it?

605
00:34:13.217 --> 00:34:15.636
STUDENT: What do we do?
The performance is tomorrow.

606
00:34:18.556 --> 00:34:19.724
What do I do?

607
00:34:19.807 --> 00:34:21.100
For me?

608
00:34:21.184 --> 00:34:22.351
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

609
00:34:22.810 --> 00:34:25.354
STUDENT 2: Hello? Mom.

610
00:34:25.438 --> 00:34:26.731
Okay.

611
00:34:27.273 --> 00:34:29.567
Mr. Song. My mom's here.

612
00:34:29.650 --> 00:34:32.111
STUDENTS: Bye.

613
00:34:32.195 --> 00:34:34.113
Guys.

614
00:34:34.197 --> 00:34:35.198
Bye.

615
00:34:35.281 --> 00:34:39.327
Go to bed early tonight.
Minseo. Take care of your throat.

616
00:34:39.410 --> 00:34:41.621
Drink a lot of water. Don't be late.

617
00:34:42.121 --> 00:34:43.664
I better watch my throat.

618
00:34:44.957 --> 00:34:46.959
(PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

619
00:35:10.483 --> 00:35:12.235
I'm going this way.

620
00:35:12.985 --> 00:35:14.529
Then I'll go that way too.

621
00:35:14.612 --> 00:35:16.364
Don't you live in that direction?

622
00:35:16.447 --> 00:35:18.407
The Earth is round.

623
00:35:18.491 --> 00:35:20.743
I'll get home one day.

624
00:35:21.619 --> 00:35:23.412
Thank you for today.

625
00:35:24.205 --> 00:35:25.206
For what?

626
00:35:26.415 --> 00:35:27.917
You were pretty cool.

627
00:35:28.626 --> 00:35:30.294
You're cool too.

628
00:35:30.378 --> 00:35:33.297
When I fell, you carried me
to the nurse's office.

629
00:35:33.381 --> 00:35:36.050
So that makes us both cool.

630
00:35:37.468 --> 00:35:38.469
It's nice.

631
00:35:39.679 --> 00:35:42.598
You like cool women, don't you?

632
00:35:47.895 --> 00:35:50.314
(DISTANT BELL TOLLING)

633
00:36:01.409 --> 00:36:03.452
-MAN: Father.
-Welcome.

634
00:36:03.536 --> 00:36:04.829
-How have you been?
-Good.

635
00:36:04.912 --> 00:36:06.372
Here.

636
00:36:06.455 --> 00:36:07.707
CARLY: (ON EARPIECE) Finally.

637
00:36:07.790 --> 00:36:09.750
MAN: Even if you can't
make it to our wedding,

638
00:36:09.834 --> 00:36:11.419
I wanted to give you the invitation.

639
00:36:11.502 --> 00:36:12.545
Thank you, Father.

640
00:36:12.628 --> 00:36:14.547
Because you've been diligent and kind,

641
00:36:14.630 --> 00:36:16.340
this good day arrived.

642
00:36:16.424 --> 00:36:18.467
WOMAN: Do you have to go?

643
00:36:18.551 --> 00:36:20.803
I feel like if you go,
we'll never meet again.

644
00:36:20.887 --> 00:36:22.263
Why not?

645
00:36:22.346 --> 00:36:24.098
You can always come and visit me.

646
00:36:24.182 --> 00:36:27.727
Did you give everyone in church
the invitations?

647
00:36:27.810 --> 00:36:30.938
WOMAN: Brother Sungchan and
Sister Jaesun and Yukyung are coming.

648
00:36:31.022 --> 00:36:34.358
It'll be a family reunion.

649
00:36:34.442 --> 00:36:36.235
You should come in for some tea.

650
00:36:36.319 --> 00:36:37.862
Come in.

651
00:36:37.945 --> 00:36:38.988
MAN AND WOMAN: Yes.

652
00:36:39.071 --> 00:36:40.072
CARLY: Let's go.

653
00:36:40.531 --> 00:36:41.741
(SIGHS)

654
00:36:50.041 --> 00:36:51.042
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

655
00:36:51.626 --> 00:36:53.461
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

656
00:37:02.303 --> 00:37:04.388
KWON DOHOON

657
00:37:04.472 --> 00:37:05.932
-Yes.
-Carly Young.

658
00:37:06.015 --> 00:37:07.350
Are you sure he's on red alert?

659
00:37:08.517 --> 00:37:10.394
It's all been confirmed.

660
00:37:10.478 --> 00:37:12.396
You think we didn't even check?

661
00:37:12.688 --> 00:37:15.191
(SIGHS) I don't normally take

662
00:37:15.274 --> 00:37:16.776
the ambiguous ones.

663
00:37:16.859 --> 00:37:18.861
So I told you not to check on him.

664
00:37:19.654 --> 00:37:21.155
After disguising as a missionary,

665
00:37:21.239 --> 00:37:23.616
maybe he thinks he's a real missionary.

666
00:37:24.909 --> 00:37:26.369
He's dirty anyway.

667
00:37:26.452 --> 00:37:28.120
Don't fall for his disguise.

668
00:37:29.330 --> 00:37:30.456
Finish your investigation.

669
00:37:30.539 --> 00:37:32.917
-(LINE DISCONNECTS)
-What's wrong?

670
00:37:33.000 --> 00:37:34.085
Nothing.

671
00:37:34.168 --> 00:37:35.503
I got Dominic's photo.

672
00:37:51.394 --> 00:37:52.812
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

673
00:37:53.187 --> 00:37:55.189
(LOW SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

674
00:38:01.862 --> 00:38:03.072
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

675
00:38:12.123 --> 00:38:13.499
Please change into a gown,

676
00:38:13.582 --> 00:38:15.501
and press the bell when you're ready.

677
00:38:28.222 --> 00:38:30.224
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES)

678
00:39:17.855 --> 00:39:19.065
(FIRES GUN)

679
00:39:32.119 --> 00:39:33.329
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

680
00:39:34.038 --> 00:39:35.331
MAN: Sir, may I go in?

681
00:39:35.414 --> 00:39:37.333
Yes, I'll get changed soon.

682
00:39:37.416 --> 00:39:38.417
MAN: Okay.

683
00:39:52.014 --> 00:39:53.015
Good.

684
00:39:55.101 --> 00:39:56.185
(SIGHS)

685
00:39:58.854 --> 00:40:00.272
(HUMMING SOFTLY)

686
00:40:01.982 --> 00:40:03.275
Mom.

687
00:40:03.818 --> 00:40:05.861
Mom, fix this for me.

688
00:40:05.945 --> 00:40:07.154
Hurry.

689
00:40:07.571 --> 00:40:09.407
(SEWING MACHINE WHIRRING)

690
00:40:21.460 --> 00:40:25.005
You know, there are
10 girls in the class.

691
00:40:25.089 --> 00:40:28.175
And I'm the only one who got his candy.

692
00:40:28.259 --> 00:40:31.137
Just for me.

693
00:40:32.096 --> 00:40:34.223
Why did he do that?

694
00:40:34.807 --> 00:40:36.350
I wonder.

695
00:40:36.434 --> 00:40:38.269
Why did Boseok do that?

696
00:40:38.352 --> 00:40:40.771
I don't know.

697
00:40:40.855 --> 00:40:43.649
Other girls must've
been so jealous, right?

698
00:40:43.732 --> 00:40:46.652
Yes. Boseok's the most popular
in the class.

699
00:40:46.735 --> 00:40:48.654
(CANDY WRAPPER RUSTLING)

700
00:40:48.737 --> 00:40:50.823
I suddenly want a candy.

701
00:40:54.076 --> 00:40:55.286
Can I have it?

702
00:40:56.704 --> 00:41:00.291
Please? I want a candy.

703
00:41:02.918 --> 00:41:04.003
Sorry, Mom.

704
00:41:04.086 --> 00:41:06.505
This is inedible.

705
00:41:06.589 --> 00:41:08.591
It's Boseok's heart.

706
00:41:10.259 --> 00:41:13.137
-(DOOR OPENS)
-(DOHOON HUMMING)

707
00:41:13.220 --> 00:41:14.513
Honey!

708
00:41:14.930 --> 00:41:16.432
(DOHOON LAUGHING)

709
00:41:16.515 --> 00:41:18.517
MINSEO: Dad.
YURA: You're home.

710
00:41:18.601 --> 00:41:20.102
DOHOON: Minseo.

711
00:41:20.603 --> 00:41:21.604
What's that?

712
00:41:22.354 --> 00:41:23.647
-(SIGHS)
-(WHIRRING CONTINUES)

713
00:41:23.731 --> 00:41:26.400
What's that? What are you doing?

714
00:41:26.484 --> 00:41:27.651
That's wrong.

715
00:41:27.735 --> 00:41:29.612
So wrong. (CHUCKLES)

716
00:41:29.695 --> 00:41:31.697
(TIGER GROWLING)

717
00:41:36.076 --> 00:41:37.495
(CHEERING LOUDLY)

718
00:41:38.662 --> 00:41:40.831
You're the coolest
in the whole wide world.

719
00:41:40.915 --> 00:41:43.167
Whoa! You look awesome.

720
00:41:43.250 --> 00:41:46.295
Minseo. You look so charismatic.

721
00:41:46.378 --> 00:41:48.881
It's wonderful. (CHUCKLES)

722
00:41:48.964 --> 00:41:50.299
Isn't it wonderful?

723
00:41:50.382 --> 00:41:53.052
Now, it's time to go. Let's go.

724
00:41:54.428 --> 00:41:57.056
Mom, can you add more shoulder pads?

725
00:41:57.139 --> 00:42:00.351
And it'll look cool
with glowing stickers.

726
00:42:04.438 --> 00:42:07.441
Any other requests?

727
00:42:08.359 --> 00:42:09.944
MINSEO: That's all for now.

728
00:42:10.027 --> 00:42:11.612
Okay.

729
00:42:13.739 --> 00:42:15.908
DOHOON: Minseo. Daddy's disappointed.

730
00:42:15.991 --> 00:42:17.034
MINSEO: Why?

731
00:42:17.117 --> 00:42:18.536
I thought

732
00:42:18.619 --> 00:42:21.747
you were a matured first grader.

733
00:42:21.830 --> 00:42:23.374
You're not in kindergarten anymore.

734
00:42:23.457 --> 00:42:24.875
Then you should be able to

735
00:42:24.959 --> 00:42:26.418
stitch that on your own.

736
00:42:27.002 --> 00:42:29.672
No first grader can sew on their own.

737
00:42:29.755 --> 00:42:33.509
(GASPS) Then you'll be
the first one in the world.

738
00:42:33.592 --> 00:42:34.760
You can do that.

739
00:42:34.843 --> 00:42:36.762
You always ask Mom

740
00:42:36.845 --> 00:42:38.722
to sew a button.

741
00:42:38.806 --> 00:42:42.810
That's a matter between Mom and Dad.

742
00:42:45.312 --> 00:42:48.691
Whatever. Mom likes me more than you.

743
00:42:48.774 --> 00:42:50.985
Never ever.

744
00:42:51.068 --> 00:42:53.529
Mom likes Daddy more.

745
00:42:53.612 --> 00:42:55.072
Right, honey?

746
00:42:55.155 --> 00:42:58.367
No. You like me more, right?

747
00:42:58.450 --> 00:42:59.577
DOHOON: No, right?

748
00:42:59.660 --> 00:43:02.788
You like me more. Say you do.

749
00:43:02.871 --> 00:43:05.374
-No, you like me more, right?
-YURA: Yes.

750
00:43:05.457 --> 00:43:06.667
Stop it.

751
00:43:07.084 --> 00:43:09.086
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

752
00:43:11.839 --> 00:43:13.674
(DOHOON GROANING)

753
00:43:23.392 --> 00:43:27.605
Why do you always want to sleep with me?

754
00:43:28.731 --> 00:43:30.149
(YAWNING)

755
00:43:34.486 --> 00:43:35.904
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

756
00:43:51.170 --> 00:43:52.171
(DOOR CLOSES)

757
00:43:55.424 --> 00:43:56.842
(DOHOON GROANING)

758
00:44:03.182 --> 00:44:04.433
Honey.

759
00:44:05.809 --> 00:44:08.187
I'm really curious.

760
00:44:09.980 --> 00:44:12.399
Is it impossible for a couple

761
00:44:12.483 --> 00:44:14.234
to do it for once?

762
00:44:14.860 --> 00:44:16.153
(YAWNING)

763
00:44:16.236 --> 00:44:19.907
If you know of anyone, please ask
if it's the same for other families too.

764
00:44:20.783 --> 00:44:22.951
-(DOOR OPENS)
-(FOOTSTEPS RUNNING)

765
00:44:26.288 --> 00:44:28.374
How come she never sleeps?

766
00:44:29.124 --> 00:44:30.125
(GROANS)

767
00:44:31.293 --> 00:44:33.462
Gosh. How come...

768
00:44:33.796 --> 00:44:34.797
(DOOR CLOSES)

769
00:44:34.880 --> 00:44:35.881
(DOHOON GROANS)

770
00:44:36.548 --> 00:44:38.926
-...she never sleeps?
-(YURA GROANS)

771
00:44:40.177 --> 00:44:42.012
Minseo, brush your teeth.

772
00:44:42.346 --> 00:44:43.764
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

773
00:44:44.056 --> 00:44:46.183
DOHOON: Oh. What's this?

774
00:44:47.226 --> 00:44:48.852
(GROANS, SNIFFLES)

775
00:44:53.190 --> 00:44:57.945
(IN GERMAN) Hey, Wolfe! It's been ages.

776
00:44:58.487 --> 00:45:00.864
You came to Korea? Today?

777
00:45:01.824 --> 00:45:05.244
We should definitely meet. Hold on.

778
00:45:06.203 --> 00:45:09.206
(IN KOREAN) It's a friend of mine.
Can he come to Minseo's school?

779
00:45:10.499 --> 00:45:13.711
(IN GERMAN) Why don't you come
to our daughter's play?

780
00:45:14.878 --> 00:45:17.506
I'll introduce you to our family.

781
00:45:17.589 --> 00:45:21.260
I'll send you the address.
Call me when you arrive.

782
00:45:22.010 --> 00:45:25.597
It's so good to talk to you,
see you soon.

783
00:45:26.515 --> 00:45:27.599
(CHUCKLES)

784
00:45:27.975 --> 00:45:28.976
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

785
00:45:30.060 --> 00:45:32.980
(IN KOREAN) I lost contact with him
a long time ago.

786
00:45:33.063 --> 00:45:34.189
He arrived in Korea today.

787
00:45:35.190 --> 00:45:37.693
Gosh. He was alive after all.

788
00:45:40.320 --> 00:45:45.325
THEATER FESTIVAL

789
00:45:46.618 --> 00:45:48.620
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

790
00:45:50.414 --> 00:45:51.665
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

791
00:45:58.213 --> 00:46:00.132
You may go in.

792
00:46:01.425 --> 00:46:02.676
This way please.

793
00:46:10.267 --> 00:46:11.977
Off the stage.

794
00:46:12.895 --> 00:46:14.938
Class One. Sit here.

795
00:46:15.022 --> 00:46:17.065
Class One. Sit here please.

796
00:46:17.691 --> 00:46:19.651
Class One sits here.

797
00:46:19.735 --> 00:46:21.153
Is everyone here?

798
00:46:21.236 --> 00:46:22.571
STUDENTS: Yes.

799
00:46:22.654 --> 00:46:23.947
Boseok and Minseo. Stand up.

800
00:46:24.031 --> 00:46:25.574
-Yes.
-Yes.

801
00:46:30.078 --> 00:46:32.790
(STUDENTS CHEERING)

802
00:46:32.873 --> 00:46:34.374
It's all good,

803
00:46:34.458 --> 00:46:35.834
but it's too flashy.

804
00:46:35.918 --> 00:46:38.045
Can you at least remove the tiger
on your back?

805
00:46:38.587 --> 00:46:42.216
What? But my mom stitched it all night.

806
00:46:43.050 --> 00:46:44.676
You need to be in balance with Zorro.

807
00:46:44.760 --> 00:46:47.262
Our hero is Zorro.

808
00:46:47.346 --> 00:46:49.598
(STUDENTS EXCLAIMING IN AWE)

809
00:46:50.390 --> 00:46:52.184
STUDENT 1: Did your mom make it?

810
00:46:53.060 --> 00:46:54.645
I want it too.

811
00:46:54.728 --> 00:46:57.981
-I want it.
-Me too.

812
00:46:58.065 --> 00:47:00.275
Me too.

813
00:47:00.359 --> 00:47:02.903
-Give me one.
-Me too.

814
00:47:07.908 --> 00:47:09.910
(PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

815
00:47:15.958 --> 00:47:17.292
You can take it.

816
00:47:21.296 --> 00:47:22.297
Thank you.

817
00:47:22.381 --> 00:47:23.465
You're welcome.

818
00:47:36.144 --> 00:47:37.980
I guess the award really works.

819
00:47:38.063 --> 00:47:40.148
STUDENTS: Wow. Minseo's so cool.

820
00:47:40.232 --> 00:47:41.233
Yes.

821
00:47:42.401 --> 00:47:45.237
-So cool.
-You're so cool.

822
00:47:45.320 --> 00:47:47.239
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

823
00:47:47.322 --> 00:47:48.949
The principal wants to see you.

824
00:47:49.032 --> 00:47:50.033
What?

825
00:47:50.117 --> 00:47:51.535
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

826
00:47:52.619 --> 00:47:55.873
What did you say?
The school superintendent's coming?

827
00:47:55.956 --> 00:47:59.209
But this is just a small talent show.

828
00:47:59.293 --> 00:48:03.255
He's going to take photos

829
00:48:03.338 --> 00:48:05.799
and run it in the local newspaper.

830
00:48:05.883 --> 00:48:08.010
Make sure not to make any mistakes.

831
00:48:08.093 --> 00:48:09.177
In the newspaper too?

832
00:48:09.261 --> 00:48:11.680
But it's not that big...

833
00:48:11.763 --> 00:48:12.973
(INHALES DEEPLY)

834
00:48:13.807 --> 00:48:15.350
His term is almost over.

835
00:48:15.434 --> 00:48:17.978
So he's nosing here and there.

836
00:48:18.061 --> 00:48:20.439
What can I do? I have to play along.

837
00:48:20.522 --> 00:48:21.690
He's my old buddy.

838
00:48:21.773 --> 00:48:23.483
We get that he's your friend,

839
00:48:23.567 --> 00:48:25.527
but this was never expected.

840
00:48:25.611 --> 00:48:27.446
It's not like he's visiting his friend.

841
00:48:27.529 --> 00:48:29.489
Don't feel pressured.

842
00:48:29.573 --> 00:48:31.325
I'm sure the kids will do well.

843
00:48:31.408 --> 00:48:34.202
They've been practicing for a long time.

844
00:48:34.286 --> 00:48:38.165
We spent a lot of budget on it.

845
00:48:38.749 --> 00:48:40.417
You know that, right?

846
00:48:40.500 --> 00:48:42.669
The Three Little Pigs
used a lot of money.

847
00:48:42.753 --> 00:48:46.173
No, we didn't spend that much.

848
00:48:46.256 --> 00:48:48.926
Well The Zorro team used wires, right?

849
00:48:49.009 --> 00:48:50.344
You even had stunt coordinators.

850
00:48:50.427 --> 00:48:52.179
The budget plan seemed a little weird.

851
00:48:52.262 --> 00:48:54.348
No, the budget, he--

852
00:48:54.431 --> 00:48:55.682
PRINCIPAL: That's enough.

853
00:48:56.141 --> 00:48:58.852
Remember. No mistakes.

854
00:49:03.148 --> 00:49:04.983
(STUDENTS CHATTERING)

855
00:49:08.153 --> 00:49:10.822
Class One. Gather around.

856
00:49:10.906 --> 00:49:11.949
Class One. Zorro.

857
00:49:12.032 --> 00:49:13.742
Zorro. Boseok.

858
00:49:13.825 --> 00:49:15.077
Minseo, come here.

859
00:49:15.160 --> 00:49:17.829
Boseok and Minseo. Come here.

860
00:49:17.913 --> 00:49:20.040
Let's recite the lines.

861
00:49:20.123 --> 00:49:23.835
Blame me for taking so long.

862
00:49:24.419 --> 00:49:27.881
Oh, Lolita.

863
00:49:27.965 --> 00:49:30.467
Oh, Zorro. I don't blame you.

864
00:49:30.550 --> 00:49:32.010
Zorro. I--

865
00:49:32.094 --> 00:49:34.262
Die, Zorro. Die.

866
00:49:34.346 --> 00:49:35.597
(IN ENGLISH) Stop, stop.

867
00:49:35.681 --> 00:49:36.682
(SIGHS)

868
00:49:37.683 --> 00:49:39.601
(IN KOREAN) I don't feel any emotions.

869
00:49:39.685 --> 00:49:42.270
You need to add more emotion in there.

870
00:49:42.813 --> 00:49:44.314
"Die. Die!"

871
00:49:44.815 --> 00:49:47.275
Can you do it? Want to try again?

872
00:49:47.359 --> 00:49:49.236
-Die. Die.
-Stop. Stop.

873
00:49:51.154 --> 00:49:53.657
What do I do? That's the climax.

874
00:49:54.449 --> 00:49:56.076
Die, Zorro. Die.

875
00:49:56.159 --> 00:49:59.246
Oh, Zorro. I don't blame you.

876
00:49:59.329 --> 00:50:01.331
(STUDENTS CONTINUE CHATTERING)

877
00:50:02.833 --> 00:50:05.711
Should I make Zorro kiss the princess?

878
00:50:09.798 --> 00:50:11.383
Wait. What's wrong with the light?

879
00:50:13.552 --> 00:50:16.179
Guys. Let's get off the stage
for a second. Let's go.

880
00:50:18.015 --> 00:50:20.559
MIRIM: (LAUGHS) Look at Minseo.

881
00:50:20.642 --> 00:50:22.144
JIHOON: Look at her eyebrows.

882
00:50:22.227 --> 00:50:23.311
MIRIM: She's so cute.

883
00:50:23.395 --> 00:50:25.689
-Take a picture of me here.
-Okay.

884
00:50:26.940 --> 00:50:28.650
-Hey.
-It's not about you today.

885
00:50:28.734 --> 00:50:31.236
-I asked you to take a photo of me.
-We're here already.

886
00:50:31.319 --> 00:50:32.821
What? You can't make it?

887
00:50:33.488 --> 00:50:35.866
Come to the assembly hall.
Call me when you get here.

888
00:50:35.949 --> 00:50:36.950
See you soon.

889
00:50:39.286 --> 00:50:40.871
He'll be here before the play ends.

890
00:50:40.954 --> 00:50:43.957
I won't believe him until he gets here.

891
00:50:45.292 --> 00:50:47.210
Where's Minseo?

892
00:50:47.294 --> 00:50:49.546
I want to take a photo
with the future movie star.

893
00:50:50.589 --> 00:50:52.049
-I'll look for her.
-Okay.

894
00:50:52.132 --> 00:50:54.301
Father, the future actress is here.

895
00:50:54.384 --> 00:50:55.844
-There she is.
-(MIRIM LAUGHS)

896
00:50:55.927 --> 00:50:57.512
Come here.

897
00:50:58.680 --> 00:50:59.681
-A photo?
-Yes.

898
00:50:59.765 --> 00:51:02.017
-JIHOON: I'll take it for you.
-With this, at least.

899
00:51:02.100 --> 00:51:03.769
-Make us look tall.
-JIHOON: All right.

900
00:51:03.852 --> 00:51:06.271
-One, two, three.
-Make us look good.

901
00:51:10.275 --> 00:51:12.903
(BOTH GRUNTING)

902
00:51:15.072 --> 00:51:17.574
STUDENT: Mr. Song told us
to come for rehearsal.

903
00:51:17.657 --> 00:51:19.159
-Okay.
-I'm coming.

904
00:51:19.242 --> 00:51:20.702
Minseo.

905
00:51:21.286 --> 00:51:23.205
Minseo, this is bad.

906
00:51:23.288 --> 00:51:25.791
Don't disturb me. I'm focusing here.

907
00:51:25.874 --> 00:51:28.835
Boseok and Jihee are going to kiss.

908
00:51:29.419 --> 00:51:31.421
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS)

909
00:51:31.880 --> 00:51:34.716
There's a kiss scene
between Zorro and Lolita.

910
00:51:34.800 --> 00:51:37.094
What are you going to do?

911
00:51:39.137 --> 00:51:40.138
(YURA GASPS SOFTLY)

912
00:51:46.019 --> 00:51:48.021
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

913
00:51:49.773 --> 00:51:52.192
I want to go home.

914
00:51:52.275 --> 00:51:53.902
I can't act like this.

915
00:51:53.985 --> 00:51:54.986
YURA: Minseo.

916
00:51:55.070 --> 00:51:58.115
Calm down and listen.

917
00:51:58.198 --> 00:52:02.536
I'm dying
and Boseok's kissing someone else.

918
00:52:02.619 --> 00:52:05.163
I'm disappointed. I'm going home.

919
00:52:05.247 --> 00:52:06.957
-No.
-Minseo.

920
00:52:07.040 --> 00:52:09.209
Minseo. Where's your homeroom teacher?

921
00:52:09.292 --> 00:52:12.796
One word from me, and he won't be able
to do that. Where's your teacher?

922
00:52:12.879 --> 00:52:15.132
How dare he upset my Minseo?

923
00:52:15.215 --> 00:52:16.633
I won't let him get away with it.

924
00:52:16.716 --> 00:52:17.801
MIRIM: I've got an idea.

925
00:52:17.884 --> 00:52:20.470
How about stabbing Lolita
with your knife?

926
00:52:20.554 --> 00:52:21.972
You have to win love.

927
00:52:22.055 --> 00:52:23.056
Okay?

928
00:52:23.807 --> 00:52:25.392
JIHOON: No.

929
00:52:25.475 --> 00:52:27.310
It's better to stab Boseok instead.

930
00:52:27.936 --> 00:52:29.229
Minseo, you're strong.

931
00:52:29.312 --> 00:52:31.022
Go stab him and make him pass out.

932
00:52:31.106 --> 00:52:32.440
Then he can't kiss her.

933
00:52:32.524 --> 00:52:34.568
That's too cruel.

934
00:52:34.651 --> 00:52:35.694
YURA: Jihoon. Mirim.

935
00:52:39.156 --> 00:52:43.535
Minseo.
Boseok likes you because you're cool.

936
00:52:43.618 --> 00:52:47.038
Even if you're upset,
if you still act like a pro,

937
00:52:47.122 --> 00:52:48.707
he'll like you even more.

938
00:52:48.790 --> 00:52:49.875
Right? Right?

939
00:52:49.958 --> 00:52:52.169
ALL: Yes.
MINSEO: No.

940
00:52:52.252 --> 00:52:53.879
(CRYING)

941
00:52:58.258 --> 00:53:00.302
Hey. No calls from Dohoon yet?

942
00:53:00.385 --> 00:53:02.846
No. Maybe he's driving.
He doesn't even read my texts.

943
00:53:04.723 --> 00:53:06.391
Minseo. Stop crying.

944
00:53:06.474 --> 00:53:09.811
I hate plays more than
anything in the world.

945
00:53:09.895 --> 00:53:11.646
I hate it.

946
00:53:12.689 --> 00:53:15.483
She's acting up.

947
00:53:15.567 --> 00:53:17.903
No one but Dohoon can control her.

948
00:53:17.986 --> 00:53:20.155
-Call him until he picks up.
-Okay.

949
00:53:20.238 --> 00:53:22.574
We must stop her before she loses it.

950
00:53:22.657 --> 00:53:24.159
Mirim, join him.

951
00:53:24.242 --> 00:53:25.327
-Yes, Father.
-MINSEO: No.

952
00:53:25.410 --> 00:53:26.870
Why isn't he picking up?

953
00:53:26.953 --> 00:53:28.371
Two, three. Get up. Up.

954
00:53:28.455 --> 00:53:29.831
MIRIM: What's his number?

955
00:53:29.915 --> 00:53:31.833
JIHOON: You don't even know his...
YURA: Oh!

956
00:53:32.709 --> 00:53:33.835
-Minseo.
-Minseo.

957
00:53:35.295 --> 00:53:36.713
CHIEF OH

958
00:53:38.840 --> 00:53:40.467
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

959
00:53:40.550 --> 00:53:41.551
(VIBRATING STOPS)

960
00:53:42.719 --> 00:53:44.387
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

961
00:53:52.938 --> 00:53:53.939
CHIEF OH

962
00:53:54.022 --> 00:53:55.523
-(CELL PHONE BEEPS)
-(LINE RINGING)

963
00:54:00.820 --> 00:54:02.656
CHIEF OH:
If it's not urgent, call me later.

964
00:54:02.739 --> 00:54:04.074
I couldn't check the last part.

965
00:54:04.157 --> 00:54:05.158
You know why?

966
00:54:05.242 --> 00:54:07.327
Information from the head office
must be true.

967
00:54:07.410 --> 00:54:10.121
Carly Young retired a few years ago.

968
00:54:10.205 --> 00:54:12.123
Why don't we report to the head office

969
00:54:13.250 --> 00:54:14.376
and wait?

970
00:54:14.459 --> 00:54:16.878
The head office already made
the decision. Finish him.

971
00:54:16.962 --> 00:54:17.963
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

972
00:54:29.808 --> 00:54:31.643
-(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)
-Oh.

973
00:54:32.227 --> 00:54:34.354
WOMAN: (ON PHONE)
I've looked up what you asked.

974
00:54:34.437 --> 00:54:36.439
It was Carly Young

975
00:54:36.523 --> 00:54:38.358
who helped Min Junki enter Korea.

976
00:54:38.441 --> 00:54:40.360
I emailed the details just now.

977
00:54:40.443 --> 00:54:42.862
He entered Korea last year.

978
00:54:42.946 --> 00:54:45.699
Yes, they have been in touch
for eight months to be precise.

979
00:54:45.782 --> 00:54:47.742
And no connections abroad.

980
00:54:47.826 --> 00:54:49.953
Any changes
on Carly Young's departure date?

981
00:54:50.537 --> 00:54:51.538
One second.

982
00:54:52.998 --> 00:54:53.999
Nothing.

983
00:54:54.082 --> 00:54:55.333
Flight at 7 a.m. tomorrow.

984
00:54:55.834 --> 00:54:58.795
I thought Dohoon was going to
handle him today.

985
00:54:58.878 --> 00:55:00.839
Okay. I'll call you back.

986
00:55:02.841 --> 00:55:03.842
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

987
00:55:03.925 --> 00:55:06.636
What if Dominic was
trying to meet Carly Young?

988
00:55:08.596 --> 00:55:10.223
What's wrong?

989
00:55:10.307 --> 00:55:11.933
How long until Dominic's boat arrives?

990
00:55:14.227 --> 00:55:15.228
About an hour.

991
00:55:15.854 --> 00:55:17.522
Let's place our agents here.

992
00:55:17.605 --> 00:55:19.482
-We're going to Seoul.
-All of a sudden?

993
00:55:19.566 --> 00:55:21.109
I'll explain on the way.

994
00:55:22.152 --> 00:55:24.237
Dominic might be in Korea already.

995
00:55:28.408 --> 00:55:30.243
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

996
00:55:34.039 --> 00:55:35.332
-Hello.
-Hello.

997
00:55:37.500 --> 00:55:38.668
Minseo.

998
00:55:39.336 --> 00:55:41.004
Do you know Minseo?

999
00:55:41.087 --> 00:55:43.465
She's very playful...

1000
00:55:43.548 --> 00:55:44.632
That one.

1001
00:55:44.716 --> 00:55:48.303
That's her. She looks just like this.

1002
00:55:48.386 --> 00:55:49.387
Minseo.

1003
00:55:51.056 --> 00:55:52.223
Kwon Minseo.

1004
00:55:53.183 --> 00:55:54.434
-Minseo.
-(PA SYSTEM CHIMES)

1005
00:55:54.517 --> 00:55:57.771
(ON PA) Neuru Elementary School
Theater Festival will start shortly.

1006
00:55:57.854 --> 00:56:00.523
All families and visitors,
please be seated.

1007
00:56:00.607 --> 00:56:02.901
No. I'm not doing it.

1008
00:56:04.402 --> 00:56:05.612
(SIGHS)

1009
00:56:18.917 --> 00:56:20.919
(PA SYSTEM CHIMES)

1010
00:56:21.836 --> 00:56:24.005
(ON PA) I repeat.

1011
00:56:24.089 --> 00:56:28.093
Neuru Elementary School Theater Festival
will start shortly.

1012
00:56:28.176 --> 00:56:31.638
All families and visitors,
please be seated.

1013
00:56:39.854 --> 00:56:41.064
Mom, what are you doing?

1014
00:56:43.108 --> 00:56:46.319
I'm trying to understand how you feel.

1015
00:56:48.530 --> 00:56:51.074
No wonder you don't want to act.

1016
00:56:51.157 --> 00:56:53.201
You gave him the cool cape,

1017
00:56:53.284 --> 00:56:56.121
and he's kissing
some other girl with it?

1018
00:56:56.788 --> 00:56:58.790
That is just wrong.
That must not happen.

1019
00:56:58.873 --> 00:57:00.083
Forget about acting.

1020
00:57:01.668 --> 00:57:02.752
Let's just go home.

1021
00:57:04.295 --> 00:57:06.005
Still...

1022
00:57:06.089 --> 00:57:07.674
That's...

1023
00:57:08.550 --> 00:57:10.468
-What about the play?
-(SIGHS)

1024
00:57:10.552 --> 00:57:13.096
Who cares?
Your feelings matter the most.

1025
00:57:13.638 --> 00:57:15.140
Mom, think about it.

1026
00:57:15.223 --> 00:57:19.310
Without a villain,
Zorro would be nothing.

1027
00:57:20.478 --> 00:57:22.397
Is that how it works?

1028
00:57:22.480 --> 00:57:23.857
Yes.

1029
00:57:23.940 --> 00:57:25.650
A villain is very important.

1030
00:57:27.944 --> 00:57:29.070
Still, no.

1031
00:57:29.154 --> 00:57:30.780
Too upset to act.

1032
00:57:31.823 --> 00:57:33.408
Remember what Dad said?

1033
00:57:33.825 --> 00:57:35.535
A true actor

1034
00:57:35.618 --> 00:57:38.496
never takes the stage personally.

1035
00:57:39.581 --> 00:57:41.040
That leaves me no choice.

1036
00:57:41.124 --> 00:57:42.250
Get up.

1037
00:57:42.333 --> 00:57:45.462
Oh, Minseo.

1038
00:57:45.545 --> 00:57:47.005
You're pretty cool.

1039
00:57:47.088 --> 00:57:48.465
I'll go ahead.

1040
00:57:48.548 --> 00:57:50.425
You should come and watch me.

1041
00:57:50.508 --> 00:57:51.551
Okay.

1042
00:57:55.680 --> 00:57:56.681
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

1043
00:57:57.932 --> 00:57:59.017
(GROANS)

1044
00:58:03.813 --> 00:58:05.857
-(ELEVATOR DINGS)
-AUTOMATED VOICE: Going up.

1045
00:58:14.908 --> 00:58:16.910
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1046
00:58:46.773 --> 00:58:48.775
-(IMPERCEPTIBLE)
-(MUSIC CONTINUES)

1047
00:59:00.286 --> 00:59:01.371
(EXHALES)

1048
00:59:21.891 --> 00:59:23.893
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

1049
00:59:32.819 --> 00:59:34.070
A change of plan.

1050
00:59:34.153 --> 00:59:35.822
We're capturing Carly Young alive.

1051
00:59:36.531 --> 00:59:38.199
I'm on my way to Seoul.

1052
00:59:38.283 --> 00:59:40.910
I'll go in with Team C.
You may withdraw.

1053
00:59:40.994 --> 00:59:42.829
-What's the reason?
-I'll tell you later.

1054
00:59:43.454 --> 00:59:44.455
Got it.

1055
00:59:44.539 --> 00:59:45.540
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

1056
00:59:50.962 --> 00:59:52.964
Yes. Promise you'll come visit me.

1057
00:59:53.047 --> 00:59:54.465
You're welcome any time.

1058
00:59:54.549 --> 00:59:58.011
I'm staying near the airport tonight
and flying tomorrow at 7 a.m.

1059
00:59:58.678 --> 00:59:59.679
Yes. Bye.

1060
00:59:59.762 --> 01:00:01.764
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES)

1061
01:00:43.556 --> 01:00:44.849
Why would the Union...

1062
01:00:45.725 --> 01:00:46.726
Why?

1063
01:01:08.581 --> 01:01:09.666
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

1064
01:01:09.749 --> 01:01:11.501
(IN ENGLISH)
Carly Young's taken care of.

1065
01:01:11.584 --> 01:01:14.671
Yeah, I talked to Min Junki
and confirmed the location of them all.

1066
01:01:14.754 --> 01:01:15.963
Consider the job done.

1067
01:01:19.092 --> 01:01:21.094
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1068
01:01:28.726 --> 01:01:30.353
(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING)

1069
01:01:30.770 --> 01:01:31.938
(IN KOREAN) Where's Raymond?

1070
01:01:32.438 --> 01:01:33.439
Raymond?

1071
01:01:34.399 --> 01:01:36.401
(DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES)

1072
01:01:37.527 --> 01:01:38.695
It's Minseo.

1073
01:01:46.953 --> 01:01:50.164
Raymond, no point
in wasting your energy.

1074
01:01:50.248 --> 01:01:52.333
Everything's been determined.

1075
01:01:58.214 --> 01:02:01.008
Nothing's been determined
between you and me.

1076
01:02:08.433 --> 01:02:09.684
Die!

1077
01:02:09.767 --> 01:02:11.728
(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING IN AWE)

1078
01:02:11.811 --> 01:02:13.771
(YELLING)

1079
01:02:15.732 --> 01:02:17.358
(YELLING)

1080
01:02:19.444 --> 01:02:20.445
(YELLS)

1081
01:02:20.528 --> 01:02:22.530
(DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES)

1082
01:02:33.583 --> 01:02:34.584
Good.

1083
01:02:35.710 --> 01:02:37.420
(IMPERCEPTIBLE CONVERSATION)

1084
01:02:37.503 --> 01:02:39.922
(BOTH YELLING)

1085
01:02:40.590 --> 01:02:41.799
(MIRIM EXCLAIMS SADLY)

1086
01:02:43.593 --> 01:02:46.471
Raymond.
Our ill-fated relationship ends here.

1087
01:02:47.346 --> 01:02:48.556
(YELLS)

1088
01:02:52.602 --> 01:02:54.854
Zorro, I'm not going to forgive you.

1089
01:02:56.856 --> 01:02:59.859
-(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)
-(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING)

1090
01:02:59.942 --> 01:03:01.778
(APPLAUSE)

1091
01:03:02.528 --> 01:03:03.988
She's good.

1092
01:03:05.114 --> 01:03:06.908
Yura, she's not a troublemaker anymore.

1093
01:03:06.991 --> 01:03:08.701
That's my daughter.

1094
01:03:08.785 --> 01:03:10.453
All right. Focus.

1095
01:03:10.536 --> 01:03:12.163
Stay alert to the end.

1096
01:03:12.246 --> 01:03:13.831
You got this, Class One.

1097
01:03:13.915 --> 01:03:14.957
STUDENTS: Yes.

1098
01:03:15.041 --> 01:03:16.542
Let's wait in your positions.

1099
01:03:16.626 --> 01:03:17.627
Yes.

1100
01:03:23.549 --> 01:03:26.636
Boseok, are you going to kill me
and kiss the princess?

1101
01:03:26.719 --> 01:03:27.845
I have to.

1102
01:03:28.387 --> 01:03:31.682
Do you want to kiss Hwang Jihee?

1103
01:03:31.766 --> 01:03:35.269
No, I'm only pretending.

1104
01:03:35.353 --> 01:03:38.564
What if you end up kissing her for real?
What are you going to do then?

1105
01:03:38.773 --> 01:03:40.149
Then

1106
01:03:40.233 --> 01:03:41.734
it's too bad.

1107
01:03:42.819 --> 01:03:44.570
I'm asking you for one last time.

1108
01:03:44.654 --> 01:03:48.074
I'm going to get stabbed
and bleed to death,

1109
01:03:48.157 --> 01:03:50.660
and you're going to kiss Jihee
in front of me?

1110
01:03:50.743 --> 01:03:53.412
I have to. The script was changed.

1111
01:03:53.496 --> 01:03:56.874
(SIGHS) Fine. I'm changing my script.

1112
01:03:58.000 --> 01:04:01.337
Boseok, what are you doing?
You need to get on the stage. Let's go.

1113
01:04:02.463 --> 01:04:03.673
Come on.

1114
01:04:06.050 --> 01:04:07.677
Minseo, can you do it?

1115
01:04:07.760 --> 01:04:09.846
-Yes, Mr. Song.
-Let's go.

1116
01:04:11.722 --> 01:04:14.350
That's my daughter. (LAUGHS)

1117
01:04:19.021 --> 01:04:20.356
NO ENTRY DURING PERFORMANCE

1118
01:04:20.439 --> 01:04:21.440
What's this?

1119
01:04:22.400 --> 01:04:24.026
I forgot to buy flowers.

1120
01:04:24.110 --> 01:04:25.486
Yura's going to yell at me.

1121
01:04:28.114 --> 01:04:29.282
I'll go that way.

1122
01:04:32.285 --> 01:04:34.537
-(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)
-(APPLAUSE)

1123
01:04:34.620 --> 01:04:36.455
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

1124
01:04:41.085 --> 01:04:43.713
Everything is over.

1125
01:04:43.796 --> 01:04:46.507
Never. Zorro never gives up.

1126
01:04:52.638 --> 01:04:54.223
Zorro.

1127
01:04:54.307 --> 01:04:56.142
I finally got you.

1128
01:04:56.893 --> 01:04:58.394
(YELLING)

1129
01:04:58.477 --> 01:05:00.229
(AUDIENCE CHUCKLING)

1130
01:05:00.688 --> 01:05:02.523
(YELLING)

1131
01:05:05.651 --> 01:05:07.987
Raymond, it's over now.

1132
01:05:09.614 --> 01:05:12.325
Zorro, you have to die.

1133
01:05:14.201 --> 01:05:15.286
Raymond.

1134
01:05:15.369 --> 01:05:16.495
Zorro.

1135
01:05:17.830 --> 01:05:19.832
(DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES)

1136
01:05:24.211 --> 01:05:25.463
Zorro!

1137
01:05:25.546 --> 01:05:27.465
(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING AND APPLAUDING)

1138
01:05:33.638 --> 01:05:35.723
You're over now.

1139
01:05:35.973 --> 01:05:37.308
That's my line.

1140
01:05:37.391 --> 01:05:39.393
(DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES)

1141
01:05:41.896 --> 01:05:43.314
(YELLING)

1142
01:05:43.397 --> 01:05:44.815
AUDIENCE: Oh!

1143
01:05:45.399 --> 01:05:47.026
(BOTH YELL)

1144
01:05:53.282 --> 01:05:55.284
(AUDIENCE MURMURING IN AWE)

1145
01:05:56.369 --> 01:05:58.204
-(BOTH YELLING)
-(SWORD SLASHES)

1146
01:05:59.455 --> 01:06:01.457
(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING AND APPLAUDING)

1147
01:06:06.796 --> 01:06:09.173
Lolita, it's over now.

1148
01:06:09.256 --> 01:06:12.426
Zorro, I knew you were our hope.

1149
01:06:13.010 --> 01:06:16.180
You made it possible, Lolita.

1150
01:06:16.639 --> 01:06:18.015
Zorro, my hope.

1151
01:06:19.058 --> 01:06:20.184
-Zorro.
-Lolita.

1152
01:06:20.267 --> 01:06:21.811
-Zorro.
-Lolita.

1153
01:06:21.894 --> 01:06:24.939
-Zorro. Zorro.
-Lolita. Lolita.

1154
01:06:25.022 --> 01:06:26.857
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

1155
01:06:30.236 --> 01:06:33.781
How about stabbing Lolita?

1156
01:06:33.864 --> 01:06:35.324
You have to win love.

1157
01:06:36.909 --> 01:06:38.786
Stab Boseok and make him pass out.

1158
01:06:38.869 --> 01:06:40.079
Then he can't kiss her.

1159
01:06:40.705 --> 01:06:43.582
If you still act like a pro,

1160
01:06:43.666 --> 01:06:45.751
he'll like you even more.

1161
01:06:48.337 --> 01:06:49.922
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1162
01:07:06.689 --> 01:07:07.898
(MUSIC STOPS)

1163
01:07:08.232 --> 01:07:10.067
(AUDIENCE MURMURING)

1164
01:07:53.486 --> 01:07:54.945
MAN: Hey.

1165
01:07:55.029 --> 01:07:56.072
Dohoon.

1166
01:07:58.032 --> 01:07:59.241
(EXCLAIMS IN SURPRISE)

1167
01:08:02.119 --> 01:08:04.538
-Hey.
-(BOTH LAUGHING)

1168
01:08:04.622 --> 01:08:05.623
Long time no see.

1169
01:08:05.706 --> 01:08:07.333
I know. It's been ages.

1170
01:08:07.416 --> 01:08:08.501
How have you been?

1171
01:08:08.584 --> 01:08:09.585
Good. How are you?

1172
01:08:09.668 --> 01:08:11.837
This is crazy.

1173
01:08:11.921 --> 01:08:13.756
(LAUGHING)

1174
01:08:13.839 --> 01:08:15.841
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

1175
01:08:19.804 --> 01:08:23.724
FAMILY: THE UNBREAKABLE BOND

1176
01:08:23.808 --> 01:08:25.643
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

1177
01:08:45.287 --> 01:08:46.539
DOHOON: She left a will?

1178
01:08:46.622 --> 01:08:48.999
Mom always liked me more than you.

1179
01:08:49.083 --> 01:08:51.669
How can you not remember

1180
01:08:51.752 --> 01:08:53.254
the last word she said?

1181
01:08:53.337 --> 01:08:55.422
Who'd claim damages on a kids' play?

1182
01:08:55.506 --> 01:08:56.632
Want to come with us?

1183
01:08:56.715 --> 01:08:58.175
DOHOON: Get him in the car. Now.

1184
01:08:58.259 --> 01:09:00.094
CHIEF OH: Find any information on him.

1185
01:09:00.177 --> 01:09:01.428
DOHOON: About that tattoo...

1186
01:09:01.512 --> 01:09:02.638
Who's that guy?

1187
01:09:03.013 --> 01:09:04.473
CHIEF OH: Both then and now,

1188
01:09:04.557 --> 01:09:06.142
all you care about is yourself.

1189
01:09:08.727 --> 01:09:09.854
Minseo.

1190
01:09:09.937 --> 01:09:11.564
DOHOON: Now I have a reason.

1191
01:09:11.647 --> 01:09:13.149
I have to protect my family.

